intensify tax collections thru formulating strategies to improve collection of real property taxes.
Management acknowledged the low collections of income for the year and attributed it on the calamities suffered by their constituents from previous years.  Likewise, they have agreed to further intensify the collection campaign by involving the barangay officials in the succeeding years.

The following courses of actions were recommended to management to address the deficiencies noted, to wit:

creation of an Inventory Committee by the Local Chief Executive  who will be responsible in the conduct of physical inventory taking of the assets owned by the municipality as well as the preparation of the required reports pertaining thereto;

maintenance of Property Cards and Property Ledger Cards by the Accounting Unit and the Treasurer’ Office s which will be subjected to periodic reconciliation in order to facilitate correction if and when discrepancies between the two (2) records occur;

require the Accounting Unit to exert effort to locate all pertinent records necessary to recognize depreciation and effect appropriate adjustments to accounts affected to fairly present the PPE accounts.

We also advised  agency officials concerned to strictly comply with   the laws, rules and regulations regarding the proper management of its assets in order to safeguard its physical existence and ensure reliability of its recorded value.
